definition.value: An acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of ascr#21.
An acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate groups of ascr#21-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
An acyl-CoA resulting from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of ascr#22.
An acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of ascr#22-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
